=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Couple 4-bromo-2-aminophenol with N-Boc-piperidine-4-acetic acid (e.g. via acid chloride or EDC/HATU amide formation), then cyclodehydrate to form tert-butyl 4-(2-(5-bromobenzo[d]oxazol-2-yl)methyl)piperidine-1-carboxylate. | Step 2: Prepare the fused NH azaindole coupling partner as the corresponding boronic acid or pinacol boronate for the fragment -c4c[nH]c5cc(F)ccc45. | Step 3: Perform Suzuki coupling of tert-butyl 4-(2-(5-bromobenzo[d]oxazol-2-yl)methyl)piperidine-1-carboxylate with that azaindole boron partner to give tert-butyl 4-(2-(5-(-c4c[nH]c5cc(F)ccc45)benzo[d]oxazol-2-yl)methyl)piperidine-1-carboxylate. | Step 4: Remove Boc (TFA or HCl/dioxane) to obtain 4-(2-(5-(-c4c[nH]c5cc(F)ccc45)benzo[d]oxazol-2-yl)methyl)piperidine. | Step 5: Mesylate the free piperidine nitrogen with methanesulfonyl chloride and base to furnish the exact target, CS(=O)(=O)N1CCC(Cc2nc3ccc(-c4c[nH]c5cc(F)ccc45)cc3o2)CC1.

